In these remarks, President Trump addresses various topics. He states that he has no knowledge about the Mueller report and is going to Florida for meetings with Caribbean leaders and trade talks with China. He accuses the Democrats of being anti-Israel and anti-Jewish for skipping the AIPAC conference. He emphasizes his administration's tough stance on border security. He dismisses the ongoing congressional investigations as a continuation of a witch hunt and urges lawmakers to focus on infrastructure and other important matters. He denies knowledge of Jared Kushner using an encrypted app to communicate with foreign officials. He reiterates his belief that there was no collusion or obstruction and calls the investigation a hoax. He expresses confidence in Attorney General William Barr to make a decision.